<subSubSection id="53F9655C7C122A2A33BCFD0ABAD09838" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1B5C36D77C122A2A33BCFD0ABAD09838" blockId="1.[151,1437,476,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A33BCFD0ABB029984" bold="true" box="[199,316,658,682]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally, 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A32C7FD0BB8509984" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" box="[444,622,658,682]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Parvuspina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tawaghatensis">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A32C7FD0BB8509984" box="[444,622,658,682]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">P. tawaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely similar to the 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A300BFD0BBE3F9984" box="[880,1025,658,682]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calamaria">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A300BFD0BBE3F9984" box="[880,1025,658,682]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">M. calamaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it significantly differs due to male genital attributes. The details are discussed under the diagnosis of the genus. The females of 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A370CFD2FBEDB99E0" box="[1143,1253,694,718]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasara">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A370CFD2FBEDB99E0" box="[1143,1253,694,718]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">M. dasara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3661FD2FBFA299E0" box="[1306,1436,694,718]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3661FD2FBFA299E0" box="[1306,1436,694,718]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">M. undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also very similar to the adults of 
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A316CFD43B8F199DC" box="[535,719,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A316CFD43B8F599DC" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" box="[535,715,730,754]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Parvuspina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tawaghatensis">P. tawaghatensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but both the former species are true members of genus 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3663FD42BAD09838" authority="Hubner." authorityName="Hubner." class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3663FD42BFA299DC" box="[1304,1436,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Miltochrista</emphasis>
Hübner.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53F9655C7C122A2A33BCFCBABB6B9F74" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" type="description">
<paragraph id="1B5C36D77C122A2A33BCFCBABB6B9F74" blockId="1.[151,1437,476,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A33BCFCBABB6C9814" bold="true" box="[199,338,802,826]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Description.</emphasis>
Wing length of 
<quantity id="DC1B9B327C122A2A317CFCBAB8699817" box="[519,599,802,826]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
. General body colour straw yellow to pale orange yellow. Antennae ciliated, base of antennae is ornamented with yellow scales. Forewing with basal area of costa black up to 1/5 length; a small subbasal black spot and a black discoidal spot; underside pale fuscous, except outer, inner, and marginal areas. Hindwing paler. Legs slightly darker than rest of the body; mid tibia with single pair of spurs, hind tibia with two pair of spurs. Male genitalia with uncus robust, almost equal to the length of tegumen, having two sub-basal, dorso-lateral spines; tegumen short, broad, attached to vinculum with a small stalk; vinculum slightly longer than tegumen; saccus broad U-shaped; transtilla with lobed apex; valva undivided, without any process, ending to a sharp apex, costal edge in form of s-shaped curve, ventral edge smoothly curved; vesica globular with an apical field of scobination, two cornuti present: one is large, second is smaller.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53F9655C7C122A2A33BCFBFEBE469F50" box="[199,1144,1126,1150]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1B5C36D77C122A2A33BCFBFEBE469F50" blockId="1.[151,1437,476,1582]" box="[199,1144,1126,1150]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A33BCFBFEBB769F50" bold="true" box="[199,328,1126,1150]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after its 
<typeStatus id="C45888757C122A2A31F4FBFEB8839F50" box="[655,701,1126,1150]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">type</typeStatus>
locality, Tawaghat in 
<collectingRegion id="D927F8357C122A2A30D3FBFEBE119F50" box="[936,1071,1126,1150]" country="India" name="Uttarakhand" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Uttarakhand</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="63F476477C122A2A3741FBFEBE4A9F50" box="[1082,1140,1126,1150]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53F9655C7C122A2A33BCFB12BBCD9D00" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1B5C36D77C122A2A33BCFB12BB089F8C" blockId="1.[151,1437,476,1582]" box="[199,310,1162,1186]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A33BCFB12BB089F8C" bold="true" box="[199,310,1162,1186]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Remarks.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B5C36D77C122A2A33BCFB36BAEF9E1C" blockId="1.[151,1437,476,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
1. We studied three specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3137FB37B93E9FE8" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" box="[588,768,1198,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Parvuspina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tawaghatensis">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3137FB37B93E9FE8" box="[588,768,1198,1222]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">P. tawaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recorded some populational variation. In both 
<typeStatus id="C45888757C122A2A3654FB36BFA69FE8" box="[1327,1432,1198,1222]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">paratypes</typeStatus>
, the vesica bears an additional, very small spine along with two spines present in 
<typeStatus id="C45888757C122A2A3094FB4ABE6E9FC4" box="[1007,1104,1234,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">holotype</typeStatus>
. The size of the largest spine in vesica is also variable to some extent. In one 
<typeStatus id="C45888757C122A2A31FAFB6EB8E39E20" box="[641,733,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">paratype</typeStatus>
(H 10/5947), valva having a small indention at middle of ventral edge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B5C36D77C122A2A33BCFAA6BEA29E78" blockId="1.[151,1437,476,1582]" box="[199,1180,1342,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
2. 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A338CFAA7BB949E78" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" box="[247,426,1342,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Parvuspina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tawaghatensis">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A338CFAA7BB949E78" box="[247,426,1342,1366]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">P. tawaghatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published as 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3117FAA6BEA69E78" authority="(Moore) in Kirti &amp; Singh (2015)" authorityName="in Kirti &amp; Singh" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Moore" box="[620,1176,1342,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calamaria">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3117FAA6B90D9E78" box="[620,819,1342,1366]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Lyclene calamaria</emphasis>
(Moore) in 
<bibRefCitation id="7F724B267C122A2A30CFFAA6BEA69E78" author="Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh, N." box="[948,1176,1342,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" refId="ref1969" refString="Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh, N. (2015) Arctiid Moths of India. Vol. 1. Nature Books India, New Delhi, 205 pp." type="book" year="2015">Kirti &amp; Singh (2015)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B5C36D77C122A2A33BCFAFABBCD9D00" blockId="1.[151,1437,476,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
3. At present, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A32A4FAFAB80F9E54" box="[479,561,1378,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A32A4FAFAB80F9E54" box="[479,561,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Lyclene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of the genus 
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A30E1FAFABE1A9E54" box="[922,1060,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A30E1FAFABE1E9E54" box="[922,1056,1378,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Miltochrista</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A37E3FAFBBEC09E54" box="[1176,1278,1378,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasara">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A37E3FAFBBEC09E54" box="[1176,1278,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">L. dasara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3677FAFBBFA89E54" authorityName="in Kirti &amp; Singh" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Moore" box="[1292,1430,1378,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calamaria">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3677FAFBBFA89E54" box="[1292,1430,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">L. calamaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A33ECFA1FBB2A9EB0" box="[151,276,1414,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A33ECFA1FBB2A9EB0" box="[151,276,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">L. undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3228FA1FBBD79EB0" box="[339,489,1414,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chromatica">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3228FA1FBBD79EB0" box="[339,489,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">L. chromatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are being shifted here to genus 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3030FA1EB9F19EB0" box="[843,975,1414,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3030FA1EB9F19EB0" box="[843,975,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Miltochrista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A308DFA1FBE589EB0" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[1014,1126,1414,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasara" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A308DFA1FBE589EB0" box="[1014,1126,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">M. dasara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32A457BE7C122A2A370EFA1EBECC9EB3" box="[1141,1266,1414,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" rank="species">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A370EFA1EBED29EB0" bold="true" box="[1141,1260,1414,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3679FA1FBFA89EB0" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[1282,1430,1414,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calamaria" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3679FA1FBFA89EB0" box="[1282,1430,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">M. calamaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A33ECFA32BB249EEC" bold="true" box="[151,282,1450,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32A457BE7C122A2A33ECFA32BB2B9EEC" box="[151,277,1450,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3259FA33BB999EEC" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[290,423,1450,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3259FA33BB999EEC" box="[290,423,1450,1474]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">M. undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A32CDFA32B8069EEC" bold="true" box="[438,568,1450,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32A457BE7C122A2A32CDFA32B80D9EEC" box="[438,563,1450,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A310BFA33B92A9EEC" box="[624,788,1450,1474]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A310BFA33B92E9EEC" authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Datta" authorityYear="2019" box="[624,784,1450,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chromatica" status="comb. nov.">M. chromatica</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3067FA32B9A79EEC" bold="true" box="[796,921,1450,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32A457BE7C122A2A3067FA32B9A79EEC" box="[796,921,1450,1474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The male genitalia of all the four species were studied by 
<bibRefCitation id="7F724B267C122A2A3272FA56B8289EC8" author="Volynkin, A. V. &amp; Bucsek, K." box="[265,534,1486,1510]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" pagination="275 - 282" refId="ref2092" refString="Volynkin, A. V. &amp; Bucsek, K. (2016) What is Lyclene dasara (Moore, 1859) (Lepidoptera, Erebidae, Arctiinae), Biologica Bulletin of Bogdan Chmelnitskiy Melitopol State of Pedagogical University, 6 (3), 275 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.15421 / 201695" type="journal article" year="2016">Volynkin &amp; Bucsek 2016</bibRefCitation>
, with a concept of 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A31A2FA56B9159EC8" box="[729,811,1486,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A31A2FA56B9159EC8" box="[729,811,1486,1510]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Lyclene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3027FA56B9DE9EC8" box="[860,992,1486,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3027FA56B9DE9EC8" box="[860,992,1486,1510]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Miltochrista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct genera. Later on, 
<bibRefCitation id="7F724B267C122A2A3677FA56BAE09D24" author="Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh N." pageId="1" pageNumber="146" refId="ref2002" refString="Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh N. (2016) Arctiid Moths of India. Vol. 2. Nature Books India, New Delhi, 214 pp." type="book" year="2016">Kirti &amp; Singh (2016)</bibRefCitation>
advocated a broader concept for 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A313CFA6AB8F59D24" box="[583,715,1522,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A313CFA6AB8F59D24" box="[583,715,1522,1546]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Miltochrista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="DCE34D547C122A2A3071FA6AB9629D24" box="[778,860,1522,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lyclene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2997EAC57C122A2A3071FA6AB9629D24" box="[778,860,1522,1546]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Lyclene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its junior synonym. Following the same, four new combinations are proposed here.
</paragraph>
